Hydrodec Group plc



18/08/2016 | Press release | Distributed by Public on 18/08/2016 13:09
Contract Win







      Contract Win
    

      Released : 18 Aug 2016 07:00
    

      RNS Number : 4886H HydroDec Group plc 18 August 2016
    

      18 August 2016
    

      Hydrodec Group plc
    

      ("Hydrodec" or the "Company")
    

      Long Term U lity Contract Awarded
    

      The Company is pleased to report that its Australian opera on has been awarded a 5 year contract for the supply of inhibited transformer and switchgear oil by Essen al Energy, a major Australian u lity. The contract includes the collec on and re‐reﬁning of all generated PCB and non‐PCB waste oils and is expected to generate over 1 million litres of new transformer oil sales over the life of the contract. The contract was awarded under a compe ve tender process, with the Company successfully compe ng against a range of new oil suppliers. Under this contract, Hydrodec will become the sole supplier of new inhibited transformer and switchgear oil to Essen al Energy. The Company expects to start supplying oil under the new contract from September 2016.
    

      Commen ng on this success, Chris Ellis, Chief Execu ve Oﬃcer of Hydrodec said "I am hugely encouraged by this contract award as it is a signiﬁcant milestone in the evolu on of the Company's ac vi es. Although it will only make a modest contribu on at the Group level, it is a very signiﬁcant contract both locally and strategically. We are delighted that our re‐reﬁned transformer oil was successful in a compe ve tender and exceeded the technical product acceptance criteria. It is further evidence of the quality of our product and provides the basis to develop similar rela onships with other u li es in Australia and elsewhere."
    




            For further informa on please contact:
          

            Hydrodec Group plc
          



            020 3300 1643
          





            Chris Ellis, Chief Execu ve Oﬃcer
          





            Canaccord Genuity
          



            020 7523 8000
          





            (Nominated Adviser and Broker)
          





            Guy Marks
          

            Henry Fitzgerald‐O'Connor
          





            Vigo Communica ons (PR adviser to Hydrodec) Patrick d'Ancona


            Chris McMahon
          



            020 7830 9700
          




      Notes to Editors:
    

      Hydrodec's technology is a proven, highly eﬃcient, oil re‐reﬁning and chemical process ini ally targeted at the mul ‐billion US$ market for transformer oil used by the world's electricity industry. MarketsandMarkets forecasts that the global transformer oil market is expected to grow from US$1.98 billion in 2015 to US$2.79 billion by 2020 at a CAGR of 7.14%. Spent oil is currently processed at two commercial plants with dis nct compe ve advantage delivered through very high recoveries (near 100%), producing 'as new' high quality oils at compe ve cost and without environmentally harmful emissions. The process also completely eliminates PCBs, a toxic addi ve banned under interna onal regula ons. Hydrodec's plants are located at Canton, Ohio, US and Bomen, New South Wales, Australia.
    

      Hydrodec's shares are listed on the AIM Market of the London Stock Exchange. For further informa on, please visit www.hydrodec.com.
    

      The informa on contained within this announcement is deemed to cons tute inside informa on as s pulated under the Market Abuse Regula ons (EU) No. 596/2014. Upon the publica on of this announcement, this inside informa on is now considered to be in the public domain.
    

      This information is provided by RNS
    

      The company news service from the London Stock Exchange
    

      END
    

